<FONT CLASS="ArticleSource"><BIG>News Roundup:</BIG></FONT> 
<FONT CLASS="ArticleHead"><BIG>Beating the Warrior Drum</BIG></FONT>
<FONT CLASS="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </FONT><FONT CLASS="ArticleAuthor">Csenicier</FONT>
<DIV ALIGN=RIGHT>
<FONT CLASS=ArticleTime>09/24/2001 05:43 PM CDT</FONT>
<DIV ALIGN=LEFT>
<FONT CLASS=ArticleText>
<b>What about the Warrior?</b><p>Absor <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000317.html">responds</a> today to a player wondering why the Warrior class is seemingly being ignored with the upcoming changes to many melee classes.<p><b>We are not ignoring warriors. In fact, the exact opposite is true.<p>Warriors are the basis for all of our melee comparisons. We relate all of the melee abilities of each of these classes to the warrior when determining where they should be. We're not adjusting the abilities of warriors to balance them with anyone else, we're adjusting everyone else to fit them properly in relationship to warriors.<p>The goal is a balanced melee and class setup. Having a point of reference is necessary to make build that system. Warriors are that point of reference.</b><p>The questioner was perhaps not direct enough with the question.  Let me try:<p>Why aren't Warriors getting anything good while the other melee classes are being upgraded?<p>Surely that was the spirit of the question being asked.  A question that Absor deftly sidesteps.<p>Take heart Warriors.  There are many components to class balance.  Things such as weapons and armor play big into the balance equation.  This is where Verant will likely toss the proverbial bone.  I would expect big things in this critical area from Luclin.  And if not...<p><b>Fired up for DAoC?</b><p>Many of the fine Fires of Heaven folks have moved on to other pastures.  But is the grass really greener?  <a href="http://www.noows.com/showthread.php?s=&amp;threadid=3599">Furor</a>, <a href="http://www.the-combine.com/CGN/etc/articletemplate.asp?articleidentity=71&amp;articlepath=%2FCGN%2Fetc%2Farticletemplate.asp">Creediki</a>, and <a href="http://www.noows.com/showthread.php?s=&amp;threadid=3597">Nino</a> are among those that offer their reviews.<p><b>Simply Enchanting</b><p>The Enchanter spell lineup has seen some recent changes on the Test Server.  <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/">Casters Realm</a> has all the <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/spells/sol.asp">latest spells</a>.  Oddly, Enchant Luclinite has been removed, for now, from the Enchanters future spell selection.  Enchanters are <a href="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_topic&amp;f=295&amp;t=000203">concerned</a>.  Enchanters were given many new targetable spells that allow fine grain control of aggro management.  Holding aggro may be about to get a lot easier.
</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
